#eNCA Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some of the funds generated from this weeks Travel Indaba will go towards relief efforts in KwaZulu-Natal. That is according to Tourism Minister Lindiwe Sisulu. Sisulu has welcomed delegates and her African counterparts in Durban on Tuesday as the event kicks off. The province has been marred by a series of problems, from  COVID-19 to looting and now the recent floods. READ: Durban ready to play host to Africa Tourism Indaba However, the South African Tourism board is hopeful the province will rise above this. SA Tourism says South Africans have proved to be innovative and resilient during times of adversity. It says it believes new projects will emerge to help boost tourism. Watch the video above for more details on this story. Tourism Minister Lindiwe Sisulu says some of the funds generated from this weeks Travel Indaba will go towards relief efforts in KZN. Sisulu has welcomed delegates and her African counterparts in Durban today as the event kicks off. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/aiHSVkjv1m